snippet.textDisplay:
While it might be understandable for Gurdas Mann fans to not appreciate this song, I feel it is a beautiful and definitely unique reinterpretation of the folk song. It would be in order to observe that music - like movies and traditions - often goes through era appropriation. Imagine Batman/Superman/Spiderman movies and comic books from 70s. They were originals then but will not be relatable for most people. Peter Parker now can't exist without mobile or local slang. Superman's feats would definitely go on Instagram. Next Mowgli's village will could have trains and electricity.

This song, similarly, will be era appropriate and enjoyable for the millions who started listening music long after glory days of Gurdas Mann. If you stop drawing parallels between the two versions for once, you would be able to see the uniqueness and freshness of this rendition. Lastly, for me the icing on the cake was how cute the vocalist is :-)
